A local Fort Greene favorite, Graziella’s has built a reputation for authentic Italian food and brick oven pizzas that are made with love. Known for their pizzas, Italian classic pastas and gelato, Graziella’s is a great option for weekday dining, take out, or when you’re yearning for a home style atmosphere while enjoying a hearty meal. I’ve tried most of the items on the menu and none have disappointed. The fried rice balls are a great appetizer, they’re also served with a delicious red dipping sauce. The gorgonzola and walnut salad is a great option as a starter or for a those seeking a lighter meal. For the main course, the pastas and pizzas are all divine. They offer a wide variety of choices to match any taste your palette may desire. As for the ambiance Graziella’s has a rooftop deck that overlooks Vanderbilt Avenue and offers a great aesthetic while enjoying your meal or sipping on a glass of wine. It’s easy to understand why this family owned and operated restaurant has built such a loyal following in the neighborhood.
